Except as provided in KRS 67C.111(2), proceedings to incorporate a city shall be commenced by a petition being filed with the circuit clerk of the county in which the area to be incorporated is located. The petition shall contain:
The signatures and addresses of:
A number of registered voters equal to two-thirds (2/3) of the voters of the proposed territory; or
A number of real property owners, the sum total of whose assessed value of real property is equal to at least two-thirds (2/3) of the assessed value of the real property in the proposed territory;
A statement of the boundaries proposed and the number of residents;
An accurate map of the proposed territory;
A detailed statement of the reasons for incorporation including the services sought from the proposed city;
A description of the existing facilities and services within the proposed territory; and
A statement of the form of government under which the city will operate if incorporated.
